        "content": "<p>In <code>Topology.ContinuousMap.Defs</code>, <code>Topology.ContinuousMap.Basic</code> and <code>Topology.Homotopy.Basic</code> the following lemmas appear with a \"deprecated\" comment (and slightly different arguments) – not the tag we now have, for these comments were added before we introduced the tag.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Deprecated. Use `map_continuous` instead. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">protected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Y</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">continuous_toFun</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/-- Deprecated. Use `map_continuousAt` instead. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">protected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">continuousAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ContinuousAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">map_continuousAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/-- Deprecated. Use `map_continuous` instead. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">protected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Homotopy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f₁</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">continuous_toFun</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But they're still being used. Can we just remove the \"deprecated\" comments?</p>",
        "id": 507124533,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1742531317
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would it still be desirable to use the indicated replacements? If so, we should do that.</p>",
        "id": 507202279,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1742539588
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>/poll Would it still be desirable to use the indicated replacements?<br>\nYes<br>\nNo</p>",
        "id": 507202593,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1742539766
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the answer is no; these lemmas allow dot notation for continuity too</p>",
        "id": 507306654,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1742571222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That argument (dot notation) could be made for any lemma of the form <code>Continuous f</code> where <code>f : SomeContinuousMapType</code>. The <em>whole point</em> of these generic lemmas is that it reduces the number of lemmas needed (from quadratic in the height of the hierarchy to linear).</p>",
        "id": 507308782,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1742571789
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You mean <code>map_continuous(At)</code>?</p>",
        "id": 507310984,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1742572371
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>right, that's the generic lemma.</p>",
        "id": 507311481,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1742572514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally, I wouldn't mind having the dot notation versions around <em>so long as we don't have to write them explicitly in the code</em>. That is, if these lemmas were autogenerated upon writing an instance of <code>ContinuousMapClass</code>, that would be fine with me, although I'm not sure if others share this sentiment.</p>",
        "id": 507312123,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1742572692
